Akaye, wizard of six seasons <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubookwormkitty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bookwormkitty</A> at: 7/20/02 5:51:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulunathreee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lunathreee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/19/02 10:56:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> gods, gods!  everwhere there are gods!<br>
<br>
i have no god.  i'm not even sure what that means.  everyone around here seems to follow one, but i've never understood the point.  i've seen shadowknights of Innoruuk and paladins of Tunare slaughter the same undead minions side by side, and still have a battle with each other over who is more 'right' afterwards.  <br>
<br>
besides, people kill these so-called 'gods' all the time, then boast about the things that littered the bodies afterwards.  if a god is a supreme being, how do you kill one?<br>
<br>
i can do without gods just fine, thanks.  if you need one to survive, then please worship them in peace.  but do not preach to me over a fine bottle of stout, and ruin my enjoyment with your self-righteousness. <br>
<br>
