<br>
Aye, I know of this Solusek Ro of who you speak. I knew another wizard that worshipped him, one that claimed to be honorable, but was not.  A hot-headed one was he, constantly looking for fights and fighting duels.  But that was long ago...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Maritzia sighs and pours herself another drink.  After taking a sip, she continues.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I also know of Tunare, the Mother of the elves.  Many of my guild worship her, and I hold her in high respect.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> A light comes into her eyes now as she continues about the deity that she worships, a light that even the drink cannot extinguish.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
