<br>
&quot;Ther' be only one god that need to be followed.  That be The Tribunal the Six 'amm'rs o'Justice.  Ther' be many evil and good things in the werld.  'Em poities kill in the name o'good, 'em inkies and fatties in the name o'evil yet ther' only one who can truly judge what be right and what be wrong, ther' be only one that knows what be just, and in the end all of ye shall be judged by 'im good, evil, man er beast, then ye will truly und'rstand the meanin' o'the sayin' &quot;The Justice o'the Tribunal descends upon ye.  T'seems that good be always jus' yet that nae be the case too much good breeds evil and injustice if ye fail to und'rstand that ye ar' nae werthy o'The Tribunal&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 539<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 2:51:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> &quot;Very well...you wish to know of the religion of the Iksar, of Cazic-Thule. The soft skins who &quot;worship&quot; our lord know nothing of him, so know that whatever they say is false. Now then...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The ways of Fear are cold, harsh, and extremely effective. Fear can be used for many things, from controlling ones enemies to keeping order in your own ranks. Through the properly applied use of fear, ones society can be greatly strengthened. By enforcing strict laws and orders, those who are corrupt are much more easily weeded out, and those who could be tainted with corruption are often too intimidated to do so. Those who are lazy and weak will often strive to become efficent and strong, knowing full well should they not they will be disposed of. Through spreading fear, one can greatly reduce the strength of ones enemies and defeat them much more easily. Through spreading fear, we appease and strengthen our lord, and help to establish order amongst a chaotic world. And do not all creatures use a form of fear? Is not law in itself a use of fear? All creatures use fear to enforce order and thier brand of justice, but few are willing to give up the few personal pleasures required to truly create a great society.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But fear is not the only tool of those of us who follow Cazic-Thule. Suffering and Pain are as well. Life is suffering, one cannot deny this. Throughout our lives we endure countless hardships, trials, aches and anguish. But we Iksar, instead of hiding from such pain, embrace it. We learn from our mistakes, and the pain we feel in our lives. By embracing the pain of our lives and the mistakes we make, we can strengthen ourselves and overcome our weaknesses, we can learn from our mistakes so that we may never make them again, and become both physically stronger, and wiser. Suffering is only somthing to be feared if one cannot learn from it. And just so you soft skins don't get confused, I am not saying we stab ourselves just to feel pain. That would be foolish. Pain is not pleasant. It is educational. Through spreading pain to the weaker races, we rid this world of those who breed weakness and chaos, and help strengthen Norrath as a whole.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We Iksar are the masters of Fear, not the victims to it. Through spreading fear and Cazic-Thule's will this entire world shall scream in anguish as the chaotic and horrid state Norrath is in dies, and a new world, one without war or hatred, one ruled through fear and strict order, is born. And that world, under the rulership of the Iksar and Cazic-Thule, shall be Norrath's greatest era.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I hope that is a sufficent answer.&quot; <p><img src="http://members.aol.com/bseh42/images/zilsig.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 7/20/02 3:19:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubookwormkitty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bookwormkitty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 9:10:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> Maladominus, with all due respect, you are wrong, in the end all of norrath will be engulfed in flame and Solusek Ro's followers will enter the flaming paradise of his home plane for eternity, so no thank you.<br>
Zildrax, even though I do not feel that your people are to rule norrath, I aggree with many of your views, I do not understand why you feel chaos is such a bad thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 541<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 9:29:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> &quot;I will tell you then, soft skin.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Chaos breeds hatred, weakness, selfishness, and distrust. If there is no order or regulations creatures freely pursue their own selfish desires with no concern of others, or lounge around lazily indulging pleasures, since there is nothing to enforce thier participation, and complain whenever they get swept up in things. One spreads selfishness, the other spreads weakness. Since creatures are free to selfishly do as they please, those who they disagree with, or those who do not desire to live amongst such selfish swine, will eventually come to hate them, and eachother. Since one can never truly trust another due to this openly accepted indulgence of selfishness, the &quot;society&quot; becomes distrustful of itself and turns upon itself, or sometimes spends many centuries merely wallowing in it's infighting. This...chaos, is often appealing to those who seek power merely for themselves. Thus the reason nearly all soft skins choose to live this way. Thier natures are selfish.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But for those who live for somthing greater then themselves and seek to strengthen not just themselves, but their entire race, such as my people, it is abhorable. Only the selfish or insane seek chaos.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Does that answer your question?&quot;<br>
