&quot;A fire raging in the middle of a battle is indeed chaotic, and if left uncontrolled will consume all it comes across before eventually dieing itself with nothing left to feed upon. However if you control the fire, as your wizardry does, then you are infact establishing order to it and commanding it, it is no longer chaotic. However the chaotic nature of wizardry is one of the reasons it is forbidden amongst my people.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubookwormkitty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bookwormkitty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 10:07:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> Zildrax, those were supposed to be two separate examples, you silly lizard, and I do not really command the forces I evoke I simply unleash them, but do not worry I know how to avoid getting burned, Oh a fire raging in a battle field that destroyed both forces would mean a victory for Solusek Ro, yes that fire will eventually die, but in the plane of sun, the fires never die. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 544<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 10:15:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> &quot;Hmm...well, if the idea of the world simply burning to ash is preferable to you, then there is little that can be said. Except that such is not preferable to myself or my people.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ulvanth>Ulvanth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 10:17:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> Aye methinks I be agreein' with this scaly 'ere in some ways, nev'r thougt I be sayin' that arharhar.  Chaos t'be bad aye, ord'r be needed and with ord'r justice.  Of course ye 'ave it all wrong. To be establishin' ord'r through pain, t'is nae just,t'is a last resort if ther' be nay anoth'r way to do it. But really t'donna matt'r if the werld will be consumed by flames er some oth'r nonsense which I fer me part donna belive.  In the end ye will all be judged by The Tribunal, the wicked shall be punished and the just shall be rewarded <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 9:25:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A request for discussion</span><hr size=1> I think Zildrax and I have much the same dream... We both want a world where every peoples lend their efforts to what makes their world a better place.  But I think the main difference is that he sees the structure of the world as the mostest important of all, and I see the peoples instead.  He sees the inherent tendency toward selfishness and hurtiness in the individual, while I see the inherent tendency toward wisdom and joy.  He sees that you hafta FORCE the world to get where it needs to go, and I see that you CAN'T force it, it has ta be an individual choice for everyone.<br>
<br>
