<br>
If you are strong, then you rule the weak. If you are weak, you try to undermine the strong or live in your proper station as prey. Only the strong are fit to rule, and if they are undermined then they are not really strong to begin with. Their strength is only an illusion.<br>
<br>
Tunare-a waste of time for worship. Yes yes, she created the elves. So? Just because she created the race I was born to, means I should bow down and kiss the ethereal ground she walks on? Just because the idiots in the Faydark champions think balance is the right path and nature is some peacefull serene place I should as well?<br>
<br>
I think not. Violence is the path to truth. Truth is power, and everything else is just a way to mask it or hide behind some philosophy that justifies your way of thinking. Without power the world is a stale, stagnant place where lemmings and sheep run free. You can try to say that because you are a certain race you are right. You can hide behind your dogma and insist you are right. You can hide and deny the truth all day and night. But in the end, it's power that everyone seeks.<br>
<br>
Power over nature. Power over death. Power over others. Power over life. No matter what you claim, you seek to have power over something. Claim whatever you wish. In the end, it's power you seek. Only the weak would lie to even themselves on that, no less everyone else. Gods can and have died before. Power is truly immortal. <p><BR>
